      "lineNbr": 110,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-23T21:42:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ELFCLASS64 instead of 2.\n\nYou should also verify that if it’s either ELFCLASS32 or ELFCLASS64.\n\nAnd, per the previous comment, it’d be nice to check “process is 64-bit” against “image is 64-bit”.",
      "revId": "ee519d37bcefddd4852adf8bf9f0cde9c1a4b551",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "057dd210_0f185115",
        "filename": "util/linux/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 19
      },
      "lineNbr": 111,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-23T21:42:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Other things to validate:\n\ne_ident[EI_DATA] \u003d\u003d ELFDATA2LSB or ELFDATA2MSB based on ARCH_CPU_*_ENDIAN. (No point in tolerating off-endian since we’re currently only concerned with and capable of reading native-endian here.)\n\ne_ident[EI_VERSION] \u003d\u003d EV_CURRENT, because if the version is off, then who’s to say that we can make sense of any of the rest of the file?",
      "revId": "ee519d37bcefddd4852adf8bf9f0cde9c1a4b551",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b034f141_7316d537",
        "filename": "util/linux/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 19
      },
      "lineNbr": 140,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-23T21:42:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think you want is_uninitialized() and not !is_valid(). There’s no point in trying to initialize it again if you already tried once before and failed.\n\nSame on lines 156 and 184.",
      "revId": "ee519d37bcefddd4852adf8bf9f0cde9c1a4b551",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
