      "writtenOn": "2017-06-23T21:42:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "DCHECK(dynamic_table_initialized_.is_uninitialized()) first to guard against multiple initialization. Since this is InitializationState and not InitializationStateDcheck, it’s on you to do the DCHECK yourself.",
      "revId": "ee519d37bcefddd4852adf8bf9f0cde9c1a4b551",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "778df08c_36393c23",
        "filename": "util/linux/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 19
      },
      "lineNbr": 211,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-23T21:42:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually, considering the other comment I left you on line 140, you might want to restructure this to allow the Initialize*() methods to be called multiple times, and make them be responsible for deciding whether they need to initialize or not. That’d keep you from having the pattern where you do is_uninitialized() \u0026\u0026 Initialize() three times.\n\n  if (is_valid()) {\n    return true;\n  }\n  if (is_invalid()) {\n    return false;\n  }\n  DCHECK(is_uninitialized());\n\n  set_invalid();\n\n  // do initialization\n\n  set_valid();\n  return true;",
      "revId": "ee519d37bcefddd4852adf8bf9f0cde9c1a4b551",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
