      "writtenOn": "2017-06-23T21:42:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Some of the things that you read are unbounded—whatever memory says an offset or pointer is, you just go ahead and read it. Is there a way to apply bounds to any of these things to ensure that we don’t attempt to read outside of the module we’re looking at? If something does point outside of its own module, it’s a bad sign…",
